Package: tweetDumpR
Type: Package
Title: Get tweets without restrictions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Magnus", "Furugård", email = "magnus.furugard@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Magnus Furugård <magnus.furugard@gmail.com>
URL: https://github.com/magnusfurugard/tweetDumpR
BugReports: https://github.com/magnusfurugard/tweetDumpR/issues
Description: This packages uses the Twitter frontent-API to retrieve user tweets nearly limitless. It has no limitations of requests per time-window, but it throttles at about ~800 tweets for a single user. Based heavily on the following Python package: https://github.com/kennethreitz/twitter-scraper/. 
Depends: R (>= 3.4.2)
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    dplyr, 
    magrittr, 
    httr, 
    stringr, 
    jsonlite, 
    tibble, 
    rvest, 
    tidyr, 
    data.table
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
